## String Transformer
 String Transformer, is a tool that takes text input from the user and applies different transformations to make it clean and readable. When you run the program, it shows a list of available commands and waits for you to type a command followed by your text. The commands are: upper to make all letters uppercase, lower to make all letters lowercase, cap to capitalize the first letter of each word, title to make a title case while keeping small words lowercase unless they are the first word, snake to convert the text into snake_case by removing symbols and replacing spaces with underscores, and reverse to reverse each word individually while keeping their order. You can type exit to quit the program. If the user types a command incorrectly or forgets to enter text, the program prints “Wrong input” instead of crashing. The tool is interactive, handles multiple spaces and special characters, and lets you quickly transform strings directly in the terminal.